# LCA‑on‑the‑Line Reproduction

This repository implements a minimal, fully‑reproducible version of the **“LCA‑on‑the‑Line”** framework described in the paper *“LCA‑on‑the‑Line: Benchmarking Out‑of‑Distribution Generalization with Class Taxonomies”*.  
It focuses on the core idea – computing the **Lowest Common Ancestor (LCA) distance** between a model’s prediction and the ground‑truth class in the WordNet hierarchy – and demonstrates its relationship with model accuracy on in‑distribution (ID) and out‑of‑distribution (OOD) datasets.

> **NOTE**  
> The original paper evaluates 75 different models on ImageNet and several OOD variants.  
> For reproducibility and to keep the repository lightweight, this implementation evaluates a handful of publicly available models on a **subset of the ImageNet validation set (e.g., 500 images)** and an optional OOD dataset supplied by the user.  
> The code can be easily extended to the full benchmark by adding more models and datasets.

